{"id":18200,"date":"2023-06-22T23:18:05","date_gmt":"2023-06-23T06:18:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=18200"},"modified":"2023-06-22T23:18:05","modified_gmt":"2023-06-23T06:18:05","slug":"the-american-dream","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2023\/06\/22\/the-american-dream\/","title":{"rendered":"THE AMERICAN DREAM"},"content":{"rendered":"<section id=\"post-headline\" class=\"post-headline-wrapper\n             default-headline\"><\/p>\n<h1 class=\"post-headline  \">You&#8217;re more likely to live the American dream in Germany, Denmark, or Australia<\/h1>\n<\/section>\n<section class=\"byline-wrapper  col-12\">\n<div class=\"byline \" data-e2e-name=\"byline\">\n<div class=\"byline-content\" data-e2e-name=\"byline-content\">\n<div class=\"byline-row\">\n<div class=\"byline-author-container\">\n<div class=\"byline-author headline-bold\"><span class=\"\" data-e2e-name=\"Matt Turner\"><a class=\"byline-link byline-author-name\" href=\"https:\/\/www.businessinsider.com\/author\/matt-turner\" data-e2e-name=\"byline-author-name\" data-uri=\"9fb042075aa209ab4b5572ac232f0d0f\">Matt Turner<\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<div class=\"byline-timestamp headline-regular js-date-format js-rendered\" data-timestamp=\"2023-06-22T10:00:00Z\" data-e2e-name=\"byline-timestamp\" data-disable-relative-formatting=\"\">Jun 22, 2023, THE INSIDER<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<section class=\"share-wrapper share-wrapper-top\" data-share-top=\"\" aria-label=\"Share This Post\" data-e2e-name=\"share-wrapper-top\" data-track-page-area=\"Post Top\" data-component-type=\"share-buttons\" data-location=\"top\" data-load-strategy=\"interaction\" data-interaction-trigger=\"share-buttons\">\n<div class=\"group-icons app-btn-width\" data-group-icons=\"\">\n<div class=\"share-icon-dropdown-container\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/section>\n<section id=\"l-content\" class=\" is-right-rail   with-rail-video-ad\" data-track-page-area=\"Post\" data-post-content=\"\">\n<section class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-12\">\n<article>\n<figure class=\"figure image-figure-image  \" data-type=\"img\" data-e2e-name=\"image-figure-image\" data-media-container=\"image\">\n<div class=\"aspect-ratio\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=700\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1280px) 900px\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=400&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 400w, https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=500&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 500w, https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=700&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 700w, https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=1000&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 1000w, https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=1300&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 1300w, https:\/\/i.insider.com\/6419ea5b1b5e1000186dbaed?width=2000&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp 2000w\" alt=\"A poverty-stricken family living in New York\u2019s Lower East Side, circa 1890.\" \/><\/div><figcaption class=\"image-caption headline-bold\" data-e2e-name=\"image-caption\">A poverty-stricken family living in New York\u2019s Lower East Side, circa 1890.\u00a0<\/figcaption><span class=\"image-source-caption \"><span class=\"image-source headline-regular\" data-e2e-name=\"image-source\">Jacob Riis\/Bettmann\/Getty Images<\/span><\/span><\/figure>\n<div>\n<section class=\"post-content typography   \" data-track-content=\"\" data-post-type=\"post\">\n<div id=\"piano-inline-content-wrapper\" data-piano-inline-content-wrapper=\"\">\n<section class=\"inline-offer pre-churn-offer\" data-offer-key=\"pre-churn-offer\" data-component-type=\"inline-offer\" data-place-after-element-selector=\".post-content .content-lock-content p\"><\/section>\n<div data-component-type=\"content-lock\" data-load-strategy=\"exclude\">\n<div class=\"content-lock-content\">\n<ul class=\"summary-list\">\n<li>The American dream promises upward mobility.<\/li>\n<li>But a child born in poverty in America is more likely to face poverty in adulthood than in many Western countries.<\/li>\n<li>Academic researchers say a stronger social safety net could help.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div id=\"formContainer\" class=\"inline-newsletter-signup headline-regular\" data-component-type=\"inline-newsletter-module\" data-event-label=\"insider_today\" data-newsletter-id=\"1\" data-list=\"Insider Today\" data-acq-source=\"economyinlinesignup\">\n<section class=\"sub-header-container\"><\/section>\n<section class=\"inline-newsletter-content\">\n<form id=\"emailCapture\" action=\"javascript:void(0);\" method=\"POST\" novalidate=\"\">\n<div class=\"desktop-error-msg error-msg headline-regular\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">The <\/span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.businessinsider.com\/what-is-the-american-dream-gen-zers-flexibility-freedom-individualism-2023-5\" rel=\"\" data-analytics-product-module=\"body_link\" data-analytics-post-depth=\"20\" data-uri=\"9989f63022ea60f506d7450c25cae4e4\">American Dream<\/a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">\u00a0might look a little different for everyone. But at its heart, it promises upward mobility, the opportunity to attain success no matter what situation you might be born into.<\/span><\/div>\n<\/form>\n<\/section>\n<\/div>\n<p>Recent research shows that&#8217;s more likely to happen in Denmark, Germany, Australia, and the UK.<\/p>\n<p>In a recent paper titled\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/osf.io\/tb3qz\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-analytics-product-module=\"body_link\" data-analytics-post-depth=\"40\" data-uri=\"eab0b8fd760b843ab21783381bc51819\">The Intergenerational Persistence of Poverty in High-Income Countries<\/a>, academics at Bocconi University and Rockwool Foundation and Stockholm University explored how poverty persists across generations in multiple countries.<\/p>\n<p>Their finding: &#8220;Intergenerational poverty in the U.S. is four times stronger than in Denmark and Germany, and twice as strong as in Australia and the UK.&#8221;<\/p>\n<div class=\"in-post-sticky only-desktop\">\n<div id=\"gpt-post-economy-desktop_in_post_ad-desktop-2\" class=\"jwplayer jw-reset jw-state-paused jw-stretch-uniform jw-breakpoint-0 jw-flag-small-player jw-flag-outstream jw-floating-dismissible jw-flag-ads jw-flag-user-inactive jw-flag-ads-hide-controls\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"application\" aria-label=\"Video Player\" aria-describedby=\"jw-shortcuts-tooltip-explanation\">\n<div class=\"afs_ads ad-placement\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<figure class=\"figure image-figure-image   \" data-type=\"img\" data-e2e-name=\"image-figure-image\" data-media-container=\"image\">\n<div class=\"lazy-holder\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"lazy-image js-rendered\" src=\"https:\/\/i.insider.com\/64932cb31465b60019987fda?width=1500&amp;format=jpeg&amp;auto=webp\" alt=\"social mobility\" data-content-type=\"image\/png\" data-srcs=\"{&quot;https:\/\/i.insider.com\/64932cb31465b60019987fda&quot;:{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;aspectRatioW&quot;:773,&quot;aspectRatioH&quot;:322}}\" \/><\/div>\n<p><span class=\"image-source-only \"><span class=\"image-source headline-regular\" data-e2e-name=\"image-source\">Bocconi University, Rockwool Foundation and Stockholm University<\/span><\/span><\/figure>\n<p>This table shows what the researchers call &#8220;intergenerational persistence of poverty&#8221; across five countries.<\/p>\n<p>The researchers&#8217; measure of persistence of poverty in the US is 0.43, which means that &#8220;experiencing all of one&#8217;s childhood in poverty is associated with a 43 percentage point higher mean poverty exposure during early adulthood (relative to an adult with no child poverty exposure).&#8221; In Denmark, in contrast, it&#8217;s just 0.08.<\/p>\n<p>That is, while an American child who grows up in poverty is much more likely to be in poverty in adulthood, a Danish child who grows up in poverty is only slightly more likely to be in poverty in their young adult years.<\/p>\n<p>The researchers found this difference between countries has little to do with differences in quality of education, nor is it based on racial discrimination or location, with the persistence of poverty in the US high across racial and geographic lines.<\/p>\n<p>Instead, the researchers find that the persistence of poverty is strongly connected to tax rates and what they call transfer insurance effects, which can be considered as akin to a social safety net.<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;The U.S. is the archetype of a liberal and residualist welfare state, featuring stratified access to higher education and employment, strong earnings returns to higher education, and a comparatively weak welfare state to insure against risks in adulthood,&#8221; the researchers said.<\/p>\n<p>Even more meaningful in the US is what the researchers call a &#8220;residual poverty penalty,&#8221; or the scars that a childhood in poverty can leave on an individual. The researchers found that &#8220;exposure to childhood poverty is particularly severe in the US,&#8221; citing for example less access to quality healthcare among low-income US residents.<\/p>\n<p>This latest research echoes many other similar findings. Back in 2017 for example, my former colleague\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.businessinsider.com\/author\/pedro-da-costa\" rel=\"\" data-e2e-name=\"byline-author-name\" data-uri=\"065ad92bbb0342cdf9aadf291b6e0e88\" data-analytics-product-module=\"body_link\" data-analytics-post-depth=\"100\">Pedro Nicolaci da Costa<\/a>\u00a0wrote that the UK, Canada, and Denmark all offered a greater chance of\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.businessinsider.com\/the-american-dream-of-social-mobility-2017-3#:~:text=Calculated%20in%20this%20manner%2C%20the,Raj%20Chetty%2C%20the%20paper's%20author\" rel=\"\" data-analytics-product-module=\"body_link\" data-analytics-post-depth=\"100\" data-uri=\"305e2af3a5e766882378692a70e67e9e\">social mobility<\/a>\u00a0than the US.<\/p>\n<div class=\"in-post-sticky only-desktop\">\n<div id=\"gpt-post-economy-desktop_in_post_ad-desktop-4\" class=\"ad ad-wrapper fluid in-post only-desktop\" data-bi-ad=\"\" data-force=\"\" data-type=\"ad\" data-adunit=\"business\/news\/post\" data-secvert=\"politics\" data-pagetype=\"post\" data-tag=\"american-dream,social-mobility,millennials,poverty\" data-authors=\"matt-turner\" data-region=\"Desktop In Post Ad\" data-responsive=\"[{&quot;browserLimit&quot;:[728,0],&quot;slotSize&quot;:[[300,250],&quot;fluid&quot;]},{&quot;browserLimit&quot;:[1260,0],&quot;slotSize&quot;:[[728,90],[300,250],[800,480],[600,480],&quot;fluid&quot;]}]\" data-tile-order=\"tile-4\" data-url=\"\/american-dream-social-economic-mobility-more-likely-germany-denmark-australia-2023-6\" data-subvertical=\"news\" data-template=\"default\" data-targeting=\"{&quot;adunit&quot;:&quot;business\/news\/post&quot;,&quot;region&quot;:&quot;Desktop In Post Ad&quot;,&quot;subvertical&quot;:&quot;news&quot;,&quot;tag&quot;:&quot;american-dream,social-mobility,millennials,poverty&quot;,&quot;tileOrder&quot;:&quot;tile-4&quot;,&quot;template&quot;:&quot;default&quot;}\" data-amazontamsizes=\"[[728,90],[300,250]]\" data-enable-ad-refresher=\"true\" data-refresh-count=\"0\" data-platform=\"desktop\" data-bids=\"rubicon:success,amazon:timeout\" data-auctions-requested=\"\">\n<div id=\"google_ads_iframe_\/4442842\/business\/news\/post_8__container__\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">More recently, research published by the Federal Reserve Bank of Chicago found that the US has relatively low rates of <\/span><a style=\"font-size: 16px;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.chicagofed.org\/research\/mobility\/intergenerational-economic-mobility\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-analytics-product-module=\"body_link\" data-analytics-post-depth=\"100\" data-uri=\"d7d0103c98d141d1bfe680b2156f4ef9\">intergenerational income mobility<\/a><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">\u00a0compared with other advanced economies, and that this mobility has been declining over the past forty years.\u00a0<\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>So yes, you&#8217;re more likely to experience the American Dream in many countries outside the US.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/div>\n<\/article>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/section>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You&#8217;re more likely to live the American dream in Germany, Denmark, or Australia Matt Turner Jun 22, 2023, THE INSIDER A poverty-stricken family living in New York\u2019s Lower East Side, circa 1890.\u00a0Jacob Riis\/Bettmann\/Getty Images The American dream promises upward mobility. &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2023\/06\/22\/the-american-dream\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-18200","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-uncategorized"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p2Ncip-4Jy","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18200","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/ww